  "why": "The paper provides a clear diagnostic explanation for why the discovered failures occur: it links error-inducing inputs to an underlying vulnerability of CNNs (sensitivity to 'continuous perturbations' that align with contiguous-sign zones in convolution kernels). This is supported by a formal analysis (Equations 1–4 in Section 3.1) that explains how matching perturbation signs to kernel zones maximizes convolution-output change and thus is more likely to cross decision boundaries. The paper also supplies empirical evidence across multiple datasets and models showing that perturbations exploiting this vulnerability produce many and diverse failures (Sections 4.2–4.3), and contrasts this with failure modes of other methods (e.g., discretization/inactivation of gradient-based white-box methods). Together the theoretical analysis and empirical results constitute diagnostic understanding that links failures to an underlying model weakness.",
